    "prompt": "<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a regular hexagon with its top and bottom edges horizontal. Three arrows extend from different vertices of the hexagon. Each arrow is the same length and represents a force. On the vertex of the hexagon directly to the left of its center, an arrow labeled F sub A extends vertically upward. On the vertex of the hexagon below and to the left of its center, an arrow labeled F sub B extends vertically downward. On the vertex of the hexagon below and to the right of its center, an arrow labeled F sub C extends horizontally to the right.\" height=\"165\" src=\"/images/1a1d80a388e45f847a42f0fbfda32f02.png\" width=\"180\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A regular hexagon of uniform density is initially at rest and free to rotate about an axis at its center. Three forces, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub A\"><math alttext=\"F sub A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>A</mi></msub></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub B\"><math alttext=\"F sub B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub C\"><math alttext=\"F sub C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>C</mi></msub></math></span></span>, have equal magnitude and are able to be applied in the direction and at the point shown in the figure. Which of these forces, if applied individually and for the same time interval, will produce the greatest increase in the hexagon’s angular speed?</p>\n",
